Overview
AgentOS is Agno's production-ready runtime that runs entirely within your own infrastructure, ensuring complete data privacy and control of your agentic system.
Agno also provides a beautiful web interface for managing, monitoring, and interacting with your AgentOS, with no data ever being persisted outside of your environment. Behind the scenes, AgentOS is a FastAPI app that you can run locally or in your cloud. It is designed to be easy to deploy and scale.

This gives you a major head start in building your AI product. Integrated Control Plane : The AgentOS UI connects directly to your runtime, letting you test, monitor, and manage your system in real time. Overview
Connecting your AgentOS is the critical first step to using the AgentOS Control Plane. Prerequisites : You need a running AgentOS instance before you can connect

Securing Your Connection
Protect your AgentOS APIs and Control Plane access with bearer-token authentication. Security keys provide essential protection for both development and production environments. Key Features: Generate unique security keys per AgentOS instance Rotate keys easily through the organization settings Configure bearer-token authentication on your server For complete security setup instructions, including environment configuration
and best practices, see the Security Key documentation.

Manual Connection Management
For explicit control over connections: async def manual_connection_example():
    # Initialize without auto-connection
    toolbox = MCPToolbox(url=url, toolsets=["hotel-management"])
    
    try:
        await toolbox.connect()
        agent = Agent(
            tools=[toolbox],
            instructions="Hotel search assistant.",
            markdown=True
        )
        await agent.aprint_response("Show me hotels in Basel")
    finally:
        await toolbox.close()  # Always clean up

## Plan

Your Agno applications are already well-structured. To integrate with AgentOS and the AgentOS Control Plane:

1. **Add AgentOS FastAPI runtime** - Wrap your agents/teams in a FastAPI app
2. **Configure AgentOS instance** - Set up session management, knowledge bases, and memory
3. **Connect to Control Plane** - Link your running instance to the web interface for monitoring and management

```diff
+ &quot;&quot;&quot;
+ AgentOS Integration for Should I Move? Application
+ 
+ This module demonstrates how to integrate the existing Agno agents with AgentOS
+ and the AgentOS Control Plane for production deployment, monitoring, and management.
+ 
+ Key Features:
+ - FastAPI runtime for serving agents via API
+ - Session management for conversation tracking
+ - Knowledge base integration
+ - Memory persistence
+ - Control Plane connectivity for web-based management
+ 
+ Usage:
+     python agentos_integration.py
+ 
+ Then connect to the AgentOS Control Plane at https://app.agno.com
+ &quot;&quot;&quot;
+ 
+ from typing import List, Optional
+ import os
+ import json
+ from datetime import datetime
+ from dotenv import load_dotenv
+ from difflib import get_close_matches
+ 
+ from agno.agent import Agent
+ from agno.models.openai import OpenAIChat
+ from agno.team.team import Team
+ from agno.tools.firecrawl import FirecrawlTools
+ from agno.tools.local_file_system import LocalFileSystemTools
+ from agno.storage.agent.postgres import PgAgentStorage
+ from agno.knowledge.text import TextKnowledgeBase
+ from agno.memory.db.postgres import PgMemoryDb
+ from agno.vectordb.pgvector import PgVector
+ from pydantic import BaseModel, Field
+ 
+ # Import custom Brave Search tool
+ from brave_tools.brave_search_tool import search_reddit_discussions
+ 
+ # Load environment variables
+ load_dotenv()
+ 
+ # ============================================================================
+ # Database Configuration for AgentOS
+ # ============================================================================
+ 
+ # PostgreSQL connection string for session storage, memory, and knowledge
+ # Format: postgresql+psycopg://user:password@host:port/database
+ DB_URL = os.getenv(&quot;AGENTOS_DB_URL&quot;, &quot;postgresql+psycopg://agno:agno@localhost:5532/agno&quot;)
+ 
+ # Configure storage for session management
+ agent_storage = PgAgentStorage(
+     table_name=&quot;agent_sessions&quot;,
+     db_url=DB_URL,
+ )
+ 
+ # Configure memory database for persistent memory across sessions
+ memory_db = PgMemoryDb(
+     table_name=&quot;agent_memory&quot;,
+     db_url=DB_URL,
+ )
+ 
+ # Configure vector database for knowledge base
+ vector_db = PgVector(
+     table_name=&quot;agent_knowledge&quot;,
+     db_url=DB_URL,
+     embedder=OpenAIChat(model=&quot;text-embedding-3-small&quot;),
+ )
+ 
+ # ============================================================================
+ # Knowledge Base Setup
+ # ============================================================================
+ 
+ # Create a knowledge base with city relocation information
+ relocation_knowledge = TextKnowledgeBase(
+     path=&quot;data&quot;,  # Load from data directory
+     vector_db=vector_db,
+     reader=None,  # Will auto-detect file types
+ )
+ 
+ # ============================================================================
+ # Load City Database
+ # ============================================================================
+ 
+ CITY_DATABASE = {}
+ try:
+     with open(&quot;data/nerdwallet_cities_comprehensive.json&quot;, &quot;r&quot;, encoding=&quot;utf-8&quot;) as f:
+         CITY_DATABASE = json.load(f)
+     print(f&quot;‚úÖ Loaded {len(CITY_DATABASE)} cities from database&quot;)
+ except FileNotFoundError:
+     print(&quot;‚ö†Ô∏è  City database not found. Falling back to basic URL formatting.&quot;)
+ 
+ 
+ # ============================================================================
+ # Pydantic Models (Reused from existing apps)
+ # ============================================================================
+ 
+ class UserProfile(BaseModel):
+     &quot;&quot;&quot;Captures user&#39;s financial info and preferences&quot;&quot;&quot;
+     current_city: str = Field(..., description=&quot;The city the user currently lives in&quot;)
+     desired_city: str = Field(..., description=&quot;The city the user is considering moving to&quot;)
+     annual_income: Optional[float] = Field(None, description=&quot;User&#39;s annual income&quot;)
+     monthly_expenses: Optional[float] = Field(None, description=&quot;User&#39;s monthly expenses&quot;)
+     city_preferences: List[str] = Field(
+         default_factory=list,
+         description=&quot;What the user values in a city&quot;
+     )
+ 
+ 
+ class CostAnalysis(BaseModel):
+     &quot;&quot;&quot;Cost of living comparison between cities&quot;&quot;&quot;
+     overall_cost_difference: str
+     housing_comparison: str
+     food_comparison: str
+     transportation_comparison: str
+     taxes_comparison: str
+     key_insights: List[str]
+ 
+ 
+ class SentimentAnalysis(BaseModel):
+     &quot;&quot;&quot;City vibe and livability analysis&quot;&quot;&quot;
+     overall_sentiment: str
+     vibe_description: str
+     livability_score: str
+     notable_pros: List[str]
+     notable_cons: List[str]
+ 
+ 
+ class MigrationInsights(BaseModel):
+     &quot;&quot;&quot;Insights from people who made similar moves&quot;&quot;&quot;
+     number_of_sources: int
+     reddit_insights_included: bool
+     redditor_perspectives: str
+     common_reasons_for_moving: List[str]
+     common_challenges: List[str]
+     common_positive_outcomes: List[str]
+     regrets_or_warnings: List[str]
+     summary: str
+ 
+ 
+ class FinalRecommendation(BaseModel):
+     &quot;&quot;&quot;Final recommendation with justification&quot;&quot;&quot;
+     recommendation: str
+     confidence_level: str
+     key_supporting_factors: List[str]
+     key_concerns: List[str]
+     financial_impact_summary: str
+     lifestyle_impact_summary: str
+     next_steps: List[str]
+     detailed_justification: str
+ 
+ 
+ # ============================================================================
+ # Custom Tools (Reused from existing apps)
+ # ============================================================================
+ 
+ def find_best_city_match(city_name: str, cutoff: float = 0.6) -&gt; Optional[dict]:
+     &quot;&quot;&quot;Find the best matching city from the database using fuzzy matching.&quot;&quot;&quot;
+     if not CITY_DATABASE:
+         return None
+     
+     city_name = city_name.strip()
+     
+     # Try exact match first
+     for city_key, city_data in CITY_DATABASE.items():
+         if city_key.lower() == city_name.lower():
+             return city_data
+         if city_data[&#39;city&#39;].lower() == city_name.lower():
+             return city_data
+         if city_data.get(&#39;display_name&#39;, &#39;&#39;).lower() == city_name.lower():
+             return city_data
+     
+     # Try fuzzy matching
+     display_names = [city_data.get(&#39;display_name&#39;, key) for key, city_data in CITY_DATABASE.items()]
+     matches = get_close_matches(city_name, display_names, n=1, cutoff=cutoff)
+     
+     if matches:
+         for city_key, city_data in CITY_DATABASE.items():
+             if city_data.get(&#39;display_name&#39;, city_key) == matches[0]:
+                 return city_data
+     
+     return None
+ 
+ 
+ def format_city_for_url(city_name: str) -&gt; str:
+     &quot;&quot;&quot;Format city name for NerdWallet URL using the city database.&quot;&quot;&quot;
+     import re
+     
+     city_match = find_best_city_match(city_name)
+     
+     if city_match:
+         return city_match[&#39;url_format&#39;]
+     
+     # Fallback to basic formatting
+     city_clean = re.sub(r&#39;,?\s*(AL|AK|AZ|AR|CA|CO|CT|DE|FL|GA|HI|ID|IL|IN|IA|KS|KY|LA|ME|MD|MA|MI|MN|MS|MO|MT|NE|NV|NH|NJ|NM|NY|NC|ND|OH|OK|OR|PA|RI|SC|SD|TN|TX|UT|VT|VA|WA|WV|WI|WY)\s*$&#39;, &#39;&#39;, city_name, flags=re.IGNORECASE)
+     city_formatted = city_clean.strip().lower().replace(&#39; &#39;, &#39;-&#39;)
+     city_formatted = re.sub(r&#39;[^a-z0-9-]&#39;, &#39;&#39;, city_formatted)
+     
+     return city_formatted
+ 
+ 
+ def get_cost_of_living_comparison(current_city: str, desired_city: str) -&gt; str:
+     &quot;&quot;&quot;Get cost of living comparison between two cities from NerdWallet.&quot;&quot;&quot;
+     current_formatted = format_city_for_url(current_city)
+     desired_formatted = format_city_for_url(desired_city)
+     
+     url = f&quot;https://www.nerdwallet.com/cost-of-living-calculator/compare/{current_formatted}-vs-{desired_formatted}&quot;
+     
+     print(f&quot;\nüîç [COST TOOL] Fetching data from: {url}\n&quot;)
+     
+     try:
+         firecrawl = FirecrawlTools()
+         result = firecrawl.scrape_website(url)
+         
+         print(f&quot;‚úÖ [COST TOOL] Successfully retrieved cost of living data!\n&quot;)
+         
+         return f&quot;&quot;&quot;
+ Cost of Living Comparison Data from NerdWallet:
+ URL: {url}
+ 
+ {result}
+ 
+ Please extract and analyze the cost metrics from the above data.
+ &quot;&quot;&quot;
+     except Exception as e:
+         print(f&quot;‚ö†Ô∏è [COST TOOL] Error fetching data: {e}\n&quot;)
+         return f&quot;&quot;&quot;
+ Unable to fetch real-time cost of living data from NerdWallet.
+ URL attempted: {url}
+ Error: {e}
+ 
+ Please provide analysis based on your general knowledge of {current_city} and {desired_city}.
+ &quot;&quot;&quot;
+

+ # ============================================================================
+ # Define Agents with AgentOS Integration

+ cost_analyst = Agent(

+         &quot;Provide comprehensive cost analysis with specific numbers&quot;,
+         &quot;If the tool fails, fall back to general knowledge but note this&quot;,
+     ],
+     tools=[get_cost_of_living_comparison],
+     output_schema=CostAnalysis,
+     storage=agent_storage,  # Enable session storage
+     memory=memory_db,  # Enable memory persistence
+     knowledge=relocation_knowledge,  # Attach knowledge base
+     markdown=True,
+ )
+ 
+ sentiment_analyst = Agent(

+     memory=memory_db,  # Enable memory persistence

+     markdown=True,

+ migration_researcher = Agent(
```

```diff
+ 
+ Your &quot;Should I Move?&quot; application now has **two deployment options**:
+ 
+ ### 1. CLI Mode (Original) üíª
+ - Interactive terminal interface
+ - Three scripts: coordination, router, cooperation patterns
+ - One-time analyses with markdown reports
+ - **Use for**: Quick analyses, development, testing
+ 
+ ### 2. AgentOS Mode (New) üöÄ
+ - Production-ready FastAPI server
+ - Beautiful web interface via Control Plane
+ - Session persistence, memory, knowledge management
+ - REST API for integrations
+ - **Use for**: Production deployment, multi-user access, continuous service
+ 
+ ---
+ 
+ ## New Files Created
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ agentos_integration.py       # Main AgentOS server
+ AGENTOS_SETUP.md            # Detailed setup guide
+ QUICK_REFERENCE.md          # Quick command reference
+ requirements-agentos.txt    # AgentOS dependencies
+ start-agentos.sh            # Quick start (Linux/Mac)
+ start-agentos.bat           # Quick start (Windows)
+ AGENTOS_SUMMARY.md          # This file
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ---
+ 
+ ## How to Get Started
+ 
+ ### Quick Start (Recommended)
+ 
+ **Linux/Mac:**
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;bash
+ bash start-agentos.sh
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ **Windows:**
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;bash
+ start-agentos.bat
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ The script will:
+ 1. ‚úÖ Check Python installation
+ 2. ‚úÖ Create/verify &#96;.env&#96; file
+ 3. ‚úÖ Start PostgreSQL in Docker
+ 4. ‚úÖ Create virtual environment
+ 5. ‚úÖ Install dependencies
+ 6. ‚úÖ Start AgentOS server on port 7777
+ 
+ Then:
+ 1. Visit **https://app.agno.com**
+ 2. Click &quot;Connect AgentOS&quot;
+ 3. Enter: &#96;http://localhost:7777&#96;
+ 4. Start chatting with your agents!
+ 
+ ### Manual Setup
+ 
+ If you prefer manual setup, see [AGENTOS_SETUP.md](AGENTOS_SETUP.md) for step-by-step instructions.
+ 
+ ---
+ 
+ ## What AgentOS Adds
+ 
+ ### 1. Web Interface
+ - Beautiful chat UI at https://app.agno.com
+ - No terminal required
+ - Works on any device with a browser
+ - Perfect for non-technical users
+ 
+ ### 2. Session Management
+ - Conversations persist across sessions
+ - Resume where you left off
+ - Track conversation history
+ - Multiple concurrent sessions
+ 
+ ### 3. Memory System
+ - Agents remember user preferences
+ - Personalized recommendations
+ - Search through past conversations
+ - Edit/delete memories as needed
+ 
+ ### 4. Knowledge Management
+ - Upload documents dynamically
+ - Add URLs to scrape
+ - Update knowledge without code changes
+ - Share knowledge across agents
+ 
+ ### 5. REST API
+ - Integrate with other applications
+ - Programmatic access to agents
+ - Webhook support
+ - OpenAPI documentation at &#96;/docs&#96;
+ 
+ ### 6. Monitoring &amp; Analytics
+ - Track agent performance
+ - Monitor API usage
+ - View error logs
+ - Performance metrics dashboard
+ 
+ ---
+ 
+ ## Architecture Overview
+ 
+ ### AgentOS Flow
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ User&#39;s Browser
+       ‚Üì
+ Control Plane (app.agno.com)
+       ‚Üì (HTTPS connection)
+ Your AgentOS Server (localhost:7777)
+       ‚Üì
+ ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¥‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê
+ ‚Üì           ‚Üì
+ PostgreSQL  Agents
+ - Sessions  - Cost Analyst
+ - Memory    - Sentiment Analyst
+ - Knowledge - Migration Researcher
+             - Team Coordinator
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ### Key Components
+ 
+ 1. **FastAPI Server** (&#96;agentos_integration.py&#96;)
+    - Serves agents via REST API
+    - Handles sessions, memory, knowledge
+    - Runs on port 7777
+ 
+ 2. **PostgreSQL Database**
+    - Stores conversation sessions
+    - Persists agent memories
+    - Vector storage for knowledge base
+    - Runs in Docker on port 5532
+ 
+ 3. **Control Plane** (app.agno.com)
+    - Web UI for managing agents
+    - Connects to your local server
+    - No data leaves your infrastructure
+    - Private by design
+ 
+ 4. **Agents &amp; Teams** (reused from CLI)
+    - Same agents as CLI mode
+    - Same tools and logic
+    - Enhanced with storage &amp; memory
+ 
+ ---
+ 
+ ## Comparison: CLI vs AgentOS
+ 
+ | Aspect | CLI Mode | AgentOS Mode |
+ |--------|----------|--------------|
+ | **Interface** | Terminal | Web UI |
+ | **Setup** | Simple | Requires PostgreSQL |
+ | **Sessions** | One-time | Persistent |
+ | **Memory** | None | PostgreSQL |
+ | **Knowledge** | Static files | Dynamic upload |
+ | **Multi-user** | No | Yes |
+ | **API Access** | No | REST API |
+ | **Monitoring** | Console logs | Dashboard |
+ | **Deployment** | Local script | Production server |
+ | **Use Case** | Testing/Dev | Production |
+ 
+ ---
+ 
+ ## What Didn&#39;t Change
+ 
+ ‚úÖ **All your existing code still works!**
+ 
+ - &#96;01-agno-coordination.py&#96; - Still works as before
+ - &#96;02-agno-router.py&#96; - Still works as before  
+ - &#96;03-agno-cooperation.py&#96; - Still works as before
+ - All custom tools (Brave search, NerdWallet scraper)
+ - All Pydantic models
+ - City database
+ - Reports generation
+ 
+ **AgentOS is additive** - it wraps your existing agents in a production-ready server without changing their core functionality.
+
```

```diff
+ ## Data Flow: User Question to Response
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 1. USER TYPES QUESTION
+    ‚Üì
+    &quot;Should I move from Seattle to Austin?&quot;
+    ‚Üì
+ 
+ 2. BROWSER ‚Üí CONTROL PLANE
+    ‚Üì
+    WebSocket message to app.agno.com
+    ‚Üì
+ 
+ 3. CONTROL PLANE ‚Üí YOUR SERVER
+    ‚Üì
+    POST http://localhost:7777/teams/move-decision-team/runs
+    {
+      &quot;message&quot;: &quot;Should I move from Seattle to Austin?&quot;,
+      &quot;session_id&quot;: &quot;abc123&quot;
+    }
+    ‚Üì
+ 
+ 4. AGENTOS SERVER
+    ‚Üì
+    ‚îå‚îÄ Check PostgreSQL for existing session
+    ‚îú‚îÄ Load conversation history if exists
+    ‚îú‚îÄ Load user memories if exists
+    ‚îî‚îÄ Route to Team Coordinator
+    ‚Üì
+ 
+ 5. TEAM COORDINATOR
+    ‚Üì
+    Delegates to agents (based on mode):
+    ‚îú‚îÄ Coordination: Sequential delegation
+    ‚îú‚îÄ Router: Single specialist
+    ‚îî‚îÄ Cooperation: All agents simultaneously
+    ‚Üì
+ 
+ 6. AGENTS EXECUTE
+    ‚Üì
+    ‚îå‚îÄ Cost Analyst
+    ‚îÇ  ‚îî‚îÄ Calls get_cost_of_living_comparison()
+    ‚îÇ     ‚îî‚îÄ Firecrawl scrapes NerdWallet
+    ‚îÇ        ‚îî‚îÄ Returns cost data
+    ‚îÇ
+    ‚îú‚îÄ Sentiment Analyst
+    ‚îÇ  ‚îî‚îÄ Uses general knowledge + knowledge base
+    ‚îÇ     ‚îî‚îÄ Returns city vibe analysis
+    ‚îÇ
+    ‚îî‚îÄ Migration Researcher
+       ‚îî‚îÄ Calls search_reddit_discussions()
+          ‚îî‚îÄ Brave Search queries Reddit
+             ‚îî‚îÄ Returns Reddit insights
+    ‚Üì
+ 
+ 7. TEAM SYNTHESIZES
+    ‚Üì
+    Combines all agent outputs
+    ‚Üì
+    Generates final recommendation
+    ‚Üì
+ 
+ 8. SAVE TO DATABASE
+    ‚Üì
+    ‚îú‚îÄ Save conversation to agent_sessions
+    ‚îú‚îÄ Extract memories ‚Üí agent_memory
+    ‚îî‚îÄ Update knowledge if needed
+    ‚Üì
+ 
+ 9. RETURN RESPONSE
+    ‚Üì
+    JSON response with recommendation
+    ‚Üì
+ 
+ 10. YOUR SERVER ‚Üí CONTROL PLANE
+     ‚Üì
+     Response streamed back
+     ‚Üì
+ 
+ 11. CONTROL PLANE ‚Üí BROWSER
+     ‚Üì
+     WebSocket updates UI in real-time
+     ‚Üì
+ 
+ 12. USER SEES RESPONSE
+     ‚úÖ Complete analysis displayed
+     ‚úÖ Session saved for future reference
+     ‚úÖ Memories stored for personalization
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ## Component Interactions
+ 
+ ### Agent Tool Execution Flow
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ Agent needs cost data
+         ‚Üì
+ Calls: get_cost_of_living_comparison(current_city, desired_city)
+         ‚Üì
+         ‚îú‚îÄ find_best_city_match(current_city)
+         ‚îÇ  ‚îî‚îÄ Searches city database (JSON file)
+         ‚îÇ     ‚îî‚îÄ Returns URL format
+         ‚îÇ
+         ‚îú‚îÄ find_best_city_match(desired_city)
+         ‚îÇ  ‚îî‚îÄ Searches city database (JSON file)
+         ‚îÇ     ‚îî‚îÄ Returns URL format
+         ‚îÇ
+         ‚îî‚îÄ Builds NerdWallet URL
+            ‚îî‚îÄ https://www.nerdwallet.com/cost-of-living-calculator/compare/{city1}-vs-{city2}
+               ‚Üì
+               Firecrawl scrapes page
+               ‚Üì
+               Returns structured cost data
+               ‚Üì
+               Agent analyzes and returns CostAnalysis model
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ### Session Persistence Flow
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ First Message:
+   User ‚Üí &quot;Tell me about moving to Austin&quot;
+          ‚Üì
+          Create new session in PostgreSQL
+          session_id = &quot;abc123&quot;
+          ‚Üì
+          Process message
+          ‚Üì
+          Save conversation to session
+ 
+ Second Message (same session):
+   User ‚Üí &quot;What about the cost of living?&quot;
+          ‚Üì
+          Load session &quot;abc123&quot; from PostgreSQL
+          ‚Üì
+          Agent has context from previous message
+          ‚Üì
+          Process with full conversation history
+          ‚Üì
+          Update session in PostgreSQL
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ### Memory System Flow
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ During Conversation:
+   Agent learns: &quot;User prefers walkable cities&quot;
+                 ‚Üì
+                 Extract as memory
+                 ‚Üì
+                 Save to agent_memory table
+                 {
+                   &quot;user_id&quot;: &quot;user123&quot;,
+                   &quot;agent_id&quot;: &quot;sentiment-analyst&quot;,
+                   &quot;content&quot;: &quot;User prefers walkable cities&quot;,
+                   &quot;metadata&quot;: {&quot;category&quot;: &quot;preference&quot;}
+                 }
+ 
+ Next Conversation:
+   Agent loads memories for user123
+   ‚Üì
+   &quot;I remember you prefer walkable cities...&quot;
+   ‚Üì
+   Personalized recommendations
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+

+ ## Security Architecture
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê
+ ‚îÇ                    SECURITY LAYERS                       ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ                                                          ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ  1. HTTPS/TLS                                           ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ     ‚îî‚îÄ All traffic encrypted in transit                 ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ                                                          ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ  2. Bearer Token Authentication                         ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ     ‚îî‚îÄ AGENTOS_API_KEY required for API access         ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ                                                          ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ  3. Database Credentials                                ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ     ‚îî‚îÄ PostgreSQL user/password authentication          ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ                                                          ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ  4. Network Isolation                                   ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ     ‚îî‚îÄ Database not exposed to public internet          ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ                                                          ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ  5. Private Deployment                                  ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ     ‚îî‚îÄ All data stays in your infrastructure            ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ     ‚îî‚îÄ Control Plane never stores your data             ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ                                                          ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ  6. API Rate Limiting (Optional)                        ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ     ‚îî‚îÄ Prevent abuse via rate limiters                  ‚îÇ
+ ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ## Comparison: CLI vs AgentOS Architecture
+ 
+ ### CLI Architecture (Simple)
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ Terminal
+    ‚Üì
+ Python Script
+    ‚Üì
+ Agents ‚Üí Tools ‚Üí External APIs
+    ‚Üì
+ Console Output + Markdown File
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ **Pros:**
+ - Simple, minimal dependencies
+ - Fast to start
+ - Easy to debug
+ 
+ **Cons:**
+ - No persistence
+ - Single user
+ - No API access
+ - No monitoring
+ 
+ ### AgentOS Architecture (Production)
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ Browser ‚Üí Control Plane ‚Üí FastAPI Server
+                               ‚Üì
+                          PostgreSQL
+                               ‚Üì
+                     Agents ‚Üí Tools ‚Üí External APIs
+                               ‚Üì
+                     Web UI + API + Persistence
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ **Pros:**
+ - Multi-user support
+ - Session persistence
+ - Memory system
+ - Knowledge management
+ - REST API
+ - Monitoring &amp; analytics
+ - Beautiful UI
+ 
+ **Cons:**
+ - More complex setup
+ - Requires PostgreSQL
+ - More dependencies
+ 
+ ## Key Takeaways
+ 
+ 1. **Private by Design**: Your AgentOS runs in your infrastructure, Control Plane just provides the UI
+ 2. **Data Sovereignty**: All data (sessions, memory, knowledge) stays in your PostgreSQL
+ 3. **Scalable**: Can scale from local development to multi-region production
+ 4. **Flexible**: Use CLI for quick tests, AgentOS for production
+ 5. **API-First**: Everything accessible via REST API for integrations
+ 
```

---

## Option 2: Use Existing PostgreSQL (No Docker Needed)

If you have PostgreSQL installed locally or access to a PostgreSQL server, you can skip Docker entirely.

### Steps:

1. **Ensure PostgreSQL has the pgvector extension:**
   ```sql
   -- Connect to your PostgreSQL database
   CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS vector;
   ```

2. **Update your `.env` file:**
   ```bash
   # Change this line:
   AGENTOS_DB_URL=postgresql+psycopg://agno:agno@localhost:5532/agno
   
   # To your actual PostgreSQL connection:
   AGENTOS_DB_URL=postgresql+psycopg://your_user:your_password@localhost:5432/your_database
   ```

3. **Skip Docker and run AgentOS directly:**
   ```bash
   # Install dependencies
   pip install -r requirements-agentos.txt
   
   # Start AgentOS
   python agentos_integration.py
   ```

---

If you just want to test the application quickly without setting up a database:

**Use the CLI mode instead:**
```bash

python 03-agno-cooperation.py
```

The CLI modes don't require PostgreSQL or Docker - they work with just your API keys.

**For first-time testing:** Use **Option 3** (CLI mode) - you can come back to AgentOS later when you're ready for the production features.

**For production/long-term use:** Use **Option 1** (Docker) - it's the easiest way to get PostgreSQL with pgvector running.

**If you already have PostgreSQL:** Use **Option 2** (existing database).

```diff
+ 
+ **Error:** &#96;Address already in use: 7777&#96;
```

```diff
+ ## Request Flow
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ USER TYPES: &quot;Should I move from Seattle to Austin?&quot;
+     ‚Üì
+ Browser ‚Üí Control Plane (app.agno.com)
+     ‚Üì
+ Control Plane ‚Üí Your Server (localhost:7777)
+     POST /teams/move-decision-team/runs
+     ‚Üì
+ AgentOS Server:
+     ‚îú‚îÄ Load session from PostgreSQL (if exists)
+     ‚îú‚îÄ Load user memories
+     ‚îî‚îÄ Delegate to Team Coordinator
+     ‚Üì
+ Team Coordinator delegates to agents:
+     ‚îú‚îÄ Cost Analyst ‚Üí scrapes NerdWallet
+     ‚îú‚îÄ Sentiment Analyst ‚Üí analyzes city culture  
+     ‚îî‚îÄ Migration Researcher ‚Üí searches Reddit via Brave
+     ‚Üì
+ Agents return analyses ‚Üí Team synthesizes
+     ‚Üì
+ Save to PostgreSQL:
+     ‚îú‚îÄ Conversation ‚Üí agent_sessions
+     ‚îú‚îÄ Memories ‚Üí agent_memory
+     ‚îî‚îÄ Knowledge vectors ‚Üí agent_knowledge
+     ‚Üì
+ Response streams back through Control Plane ‚Üí Browser
+     ‚Üì
+ USER SEES: Complete recommendation with all analyses
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ## Database Schema
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;sql
+ -- Session Management
+ CREATE TABLE agent_sessions (
+     session_id VARCHAR PRIMARY KEY,
+     agent_id VARCHAR NOT NULL,
+     user_id VARCHAR,
+     messages JSONB NOT NULL,
+     created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
+     updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
+ );
+ 
+ -- Memory Storage
+ CREATE TABLE agent_memory (
+     memory_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
+     agent_id VARCHAR NOT NULL,
+     user_id VARCHAR NOT NULL,
+     content TEXT NOT NULL,
+     metadata JSONB,
+     created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
+ );
+ 
+ -- Knowledge Base (with pgvector)
+ CREATE TABLE agent_knowledge (
+     id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
+     content TEXT NOT NULL,
+     embedding VECTOR(1536),  -- OpenAI embedding dimension
+     metadata JSONB,
+     created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
+ );
+ 
+ CREATE INDEX ON agent_knowledge USING ivfflat (embedding vector_cosine_ops);
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ## Component Interactions
+ 
+ ### Agent Tool Execution
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ Agent: &quot;I need cost data&quot;
+     ‚Üì
+ Call: get_cost_of_living_comparison(&quot;Seattle&quot;, &quot;Austin&quot;)
+     ‚Üì
+     ‚îú‚îÄ find_best_city_match(&quot;Seattle&quot;)
+     ‚îÇ  ‚îî‚îÄ Returns: &quot;seattle-wa&quot;
+     ‚îÇ
+     ‚îú‚îÄ find_best_city_match(&quot;Austin&quot;)
+     ‚îÇ  ‚îî‚îÄ Returns: &quot;austin-tx&quot;
+     ‚îÇ
+     ‚îî‚îÄ Build URL: nerdwallet.com/...compare/seattle-wa-vs-austin-tx
+        ‚Üì
+        Firecrawl scrapes page
+        ‚Üì
+        Returns: Structured cost data
+        ‚Üì
+        Agent analyzes ‚Üí CostAnalysis model
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ### Session Persistence
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ FIRST MESSAGE:
+ User: &quot;Tell me about Austin&quot;
+     ‚Üì
+ Create session_id = &quot;abc123&quot;
+ Save to agent_sessions table
+     ‚Üì
+ Response sent
+ 
+ SECOND MESSAGE:
+ User: &quot;What about cost of living?&quot;
+     ‚Üì
+ Load session &quot;abc123&quot; from database
+     ‚Üì
+ Agent has full context from previous message
+     ‚Üì
+ Process with conversation history
+     ‚Üì
+ Update session in database
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ### Memory System
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ DURING CONVERSATION:
+ Agent observes: &quot;User prefers walkable cities&quot;
+     ‚Üì
+ Extract as memory
+     ‚Üì
+ INSERT INTO agent_memory (
+     user_id: &quot;user123&quot;,
+     agent_id: &quot;sentiment-analyst&quot;,
+     content: &quot;User prefers walkable cities&quot;,
+     metadata: {&quot;category&quot;: &quot;preference&quot;}
+ )
+ 
+ NEXT CONVERSATION:
+ Agent loads memories for user123
+     ‚Üì
+ &quot;I remember you prefer walkable cities...&quot;
+     ‚Üì
+ Personalized recommendation
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+

+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ## Comparison: CLI vs AgentOS
+ 
+ ### CLI Architecture
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ Terminal
+    ‚Üì
+ Python Script (*.py)
+    ‚Üì
+ Agents
+    ‚îú‚îÄ Cost Analyst
+    ‚îú‚îÄ Sentiment Analyst
+    ‚îî‚îÄ Migration Researcher
+    ‚Üì
+ Tools ‚Üí External APIs
+    ‚îú‚îÄ Firecrawl (NerdWallet)
+    ‚îî‚îÄ Brave Search (Reddit)
+    ‚Üì
+ Console Output
+    ‚îî‚îÄ Markdown Report (reports/*.md)
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ **Characteristics:**
+ - ‚úÖ Simple: No database, no server
+ - ‚úÖ Fast: Direct execution
+ - ‚ùå No persistence: One-time run
+ - ‚ùå Single user only
+ - ‚ùå No API access
+ 
+ ### AgentOS Architecture
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ Browser ‚Üí Control Plane ‚Üí FastAPI Server
+                               ‚Üì
+                          PostgreSQL
+                               ‚Üì
+                            Agents
+                               ‚Üì
+                        Tools ‚Üí APIs
+                               ‚Üì
+                     Web UI + API Response
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ **Characteristics:**
+ - ‚úÖ Multi-user: Concurrent sessions
+ - ‚úÖ Persistent: Sessions + memory
+ - ‚úÖ API: REST endpoints
+ - ‚úÖ Monitoring: Dashboard + metrics
+ - ‚ùå Complex: Requires database
+ - ‚ùå Setup: More dependencies
+ 
+ ## Technology Stack
+ 
+ ### AgentOS Stack
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê
+ ‚îÇ         Frontend (Browser)              ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ  ‚Ä¢ Control Plane UI (app.agno.com)     ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ  ‚Ä¢ WebSocket for real-time updates     ‚îÇ
+ ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò
+                   ‚îÇ
+ ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñº‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê
+ ‚îÇ         Backend (Your Server)           ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ  ‚Ä¢ Python 3.11+                        ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ  ‚Ä¢ FastAPI (REST API framework)        ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ  ‚Ä¢ Uvicorn (ASGI server)               ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ  ‚Ä¢ Agno (agent framework)              ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ  ‚Ä¢ SQLAlchemy (ORM)                    ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ  ‚Ä¢ psycopg (PostgreSQL driver)         ‚îÇ
+ ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò
+                   ‚îÇ
+ ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñº‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê
+ ‚îÇ         Database                        ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ  ‚Ä¢ PostgreSQL 16                       ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ  ‚Ä¢ pgvector extension                  ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ  ‚Ä¢ Vector similarity search            ‚îÇ
+ ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò
+ 
+ ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê
+ ‚îÇ         External APIs                   ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ  ‚Ä¢ OpenAI (GPT-4o-mini, embeddings)    ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ  ‚Ä¢ Firecrawl (web scraping)            ‚îÇ
+ ‚îÇ  ‚Ä¢ Brave Search (Reddit data)          ‚îÇ
+ ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ## Data Flow Patterns
+ 
+ ### Pattern 1: Stateless Request (No Session)
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ Request ‚Üí AgentOS ‚Üí Process ‚Üí Response
+              ‚Üì
+         No persistence
+         Fresh context
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ### Pattern 2: Stateful Session
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ Request ‚Üí Load Session ‚Üí Add to History ‚Üí Process ‚Üí Save Session ‚Üí Response
+              ‚Üì              ‚Üì                           ‚Üì
+         PostgreSQL    Conversation          agent_sessions table
+                         Context
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ### Pattern 3: Memory-Enhanced
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ Request ‚Üí Load Session + Memories ‚Üí Process with Context ‚Üí Save Updates
+              ‚Üì              ‚Üì                                    ‚Üì
+         agent_sessions  agent_memory                 Both tables updated
+         
+ Agent knows:
+ - Previous conversations (session)
+ - User preferences (memories)
+ - Historical patterns (memories)
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ## Scaling Considerations
+ 
+ ### Vertical Scaling
+ - Increase server CPU/RAM
+ - Larger PostgreSQL instance
+ - More agent workers
+ 
+ ### Horizontal Scaling
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê
+ ‚îÇ       Load Balancer             ‚îÇ
+ ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò
+    ‚îÇ       ‚îÇ       ‚îÇ          ‚îÇ
+ ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñº‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñº‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñº‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê  ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñº‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê
+ ‚îÇ Pod1‚îÇ ‚îÇ Pod2‚îÇ ‚îÇ Pod3‚îÇ  ‚îÇ PodN‚îÇ
+ ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò
+    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¥‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¥‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò
+               ‚îÇ
+     ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñº‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê
+     ‚îÇ  Shared PostgreSQL ‚îÇ
+     ‚îÇ  (or read replicas)‚îÇ
+     ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ### Performance Optimization
+ - Connection pooling
+ - Query optimization
+ - Vector index tuning (pgvector)
+ - Caching layer (Redis)
+ - Async processing
+ 
+ ## Key Design Decisions
+ 
+ 1. **Private by Design**
+    - Control Plane doesn&#39;t store data
+    - All data in your PostgreSQL
+    - Direct browser ‚Üî server connection
+ 
+ 2. **Agent Reusability**
+    - Same agents work in CLI and AgentOS
+    - No code duplication
+    - Easy maintenance
+ 
+ 3. **Session-First**
+    - Every conversation can be a session
+    - Optional: anonymous sessions
+    - User-scoped memories
+ 
+ 4. **Tool Flexibility**
+    - Custom tools (Brave, NerdWallet)
+    - Easy to add new tools
+    - Tools work in both modes
+ 
+ 5. **Standard Tech Stack**
+    - FastAPI (industry standard)
+    - PostgreSQL (proven, reliable)
+    - OpenAI (standardized models)
+ 
+ ---
+ 
+ **For implementation details, see:** &#96;agentos_integration.py&#96;
+ 
+ **For usage instructions, see:** &#96;GETTING_STARTED.md&#96;
```
